animal.description:
NOW ACCEPTING APPLICATIONS FOR: THE REINDEER GANG!!

These 9 "Reindeers" came to us late December 2020 as owner surrenders from our local community of Anza. We are working with the owners to get the parents AND any other dogs on the property spayed/neutered so there will be no more unwanted, accidental litters.
PLEASE NOTE: We will only be posting 3 puppies at a time from this litter until all are adopted.

Their DOB is estimated to be 11/18/2020. These puppies are just wiggly, happy, fun loving, and just your picture perfect puppies. They are very well socialized and are all living in foster homes with other dogs and children. Just like your typical puppy, they love to play, play, and play ALLL day and when they're tuckered out for the afternoon, they love nothing more than snuggling up to recharge for round two of playtime. These babies are going to be BIG and just like your typical puppy, they are going to need families who are enthusiastic and dedicated to continue their training and socializing so they can remain the best pups in town!!

***PLEASE NOTE: These babies are expected to be 60-70 lbs at least when full grown. They are NOT suitable for apartment lifestyle and will need homes with yards to accommodate daily games of play and preferably another dog in the home to play, cuddle, and socialize with.

If interested in ADOPTING, please fill out an adoption application online:

animal.description:
MEET MARS, an handsome, friendly and fun-loving 2 year old boxer, hound, terrier mix looking for a loving home preferably with an active guardian and a friendly, non-senior, active resident dog. He is being kenneled in the South and his guardians shares:

"Mars is 85lbs. He is very friendly, affectionate and loving. Poor Mars spent most of his life tied to a chain outside. No one paid much attention to him... they would just feed him but no walk or playtime. Maybe that's why he gets so excited and greets new people with wiggles and wags and kisses too. He gets along with other friendly dogs well and would be best paired with another dog of similar size. He doesn't like cats at all. He does loves to go on walks and might make a great jogging companion. He is a smart pup and treat and praise motivated. He needs basic obedience and command training using force free, positive reinforcement methods. He is such a sweet loving boy who deserves a great forever home where he will be loved and adored. In return he will give you his heart."

He is neutered and up to date on age-appropriate vaccines. His adoption fee is $425. Please note that training is highly recommended for all dogs. As with all rescue animals, breed determination cannot be validated without genetic testing.

THANKS FOR ADOPTING AND SAVING A LIFE; you are MARS' hero!

animal.description: You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Tall, dark and handsome male searching for an active companion to enjoy activities that keep the mind and body in tip top shape! Hi! My name is Dutch and I'm a 75 lb, two year old Dutch/German Shepherd boy. I really enjoy hanging out with other large, energetic dogs, but I'm not a fan of the kitties, so a home with cats wouldn't be a good fit. I haven't ever played before, but I'm starting to learn how much fun it is! I'm friendly with people, but because of my size and energy level, it's best I go to a home with older children only. My foster family doesn't know my back story, but they think I might have been an outside dog because I didn't come to them fully housebroken. I'm doing much better with it, but I'll need an adopter that will take me outside often and continue my training. I have a lot of energy, so if you're looking for a hiking or jogging buddy, I'm your guy! I also really like to learn. My foster family has been diligently working with me and I've just about mastered all of the key commands! We're still working on how mouthy I am, though. My foster mom thinks it's because I wasn't ever corrected or taught boundaries when I was a puppy. I'm mostly crate trained, but I can be pretty vocal for a bit before settling down. It's just my way of telling you to come back and that I miss you!! I love peanut butter filled Kongs, though, so if you give me one of those I'll be a very happy boy! Overall I'm a sweet, goofy boy who just wants a family that will show me love and is willing to continue my training. If you are interested in adopting me, please reach out to your adoption coordinator. If you do not have an adoption coordinator, please fill out an adoption application at https://freedomgermanshepherdrescue.org Dutch is being fostered outside of Fayetteville.

animal.description:
GARY INDIANA:  NEEDS FOSTER OR ADOPT

Meet Luna.  She is looking for either a foster, foster-to-adopt or adoption.
She was originally bought to be a working dog but that did not work out for her.  Her owner gave her away and then *that" person gave her away and the third owner didn't have a fence and did not care if she ran around the neighborhood.  So, finally, she was picked up as a stray and the 3rd owner didn't want to reclaim her since they couldn't keep her home without a fence.

We are really hoping that Luna's next home will be with someone who will truly love her and care for her properly.

Luna is appx 1.5 years old, giving her an appx DOB of July 2019.  She weighs 75 lbs right now but will continue to fill out as she matures. She is heartworm and lyme negative.

Luna is good with male dogs.  She should be the only female dog in the home. 
She is going to do best in a home without cats or chickens.
Luna has not been evaluated with children so no youngsters, please.

Transport assistance within 1000 miles may be available depending on where you live and the availability of volunteer drivers along the route.

Please email for more information asdrescue@gmail.com

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.We are happy to announce that our sweet boy Casper is ready to find his forever home. Casper was surrendered by his Texas family when he needed them the most. He was a sick little man who needed medical attention and instead his family tuned him over to be euthanized. That was not going to happen if we had anything to say about that. When he arrived, Casper had a cough and in horrible need of a dental. His teeth were literally falling out of his mouth on the ride home from transport. We quickly made an appointment with our vet to help this spunky senior out. He had hair loss due to alopecia, a raging UTI, chronic bronchitis, and a fused spine. Not to mention that he suffers from mild seizures. Once many of his teeth were removed, we could tell Casper felt much better.

As you can tell Casper has a variety of medical issues and needs a home that is capable of providing him with his on going needs. He does need to remain on the steroids for life. As for the seizures, because they are so mild and infrequent he does not need medication at this time. Casper is a very happy, sweet, loving guy. He has spurts of energy where he just wants to play on your hand. He does enjoy sitting on the couch with you while watching TV or sleeping in a bed in front of the heat vent. This boy is full of kisses. Casper will sit there licking your hands or face for 20 minutes at a time. He gets along great with other dogs, but has no interest in playing with them. He would much rather sit on your lap or lay under a blanket with his favorite people. Casper sleeps in bed with his mama every night. He rarely wakes up to go outside. He is crate trained but he does not spend much time in it. During the day, while his foster family is at work, Casper will sleep away in his bed. They will leave him a potty pad to use if needed, but it is often dry when they get home. His foster family loves everything about him from his crazy hair, to his funny bark that reminds them of a pirate. They will be sad to see him leave but happy for him to call a home of his own. If you think you can provide the love and continued medical care he needs make sure you apply.

Casper is neutered, up to date with vaccines, microchipped, flea/worm treated and tested neg. for heartworm. He was also given a dental! Casper's adoption fee is $100

animal.description: Martha May is a ten-year-old, 90-lb German Shepherd mix currently being fostered in Sarasota, FL (Sarasota County). She is a fantastic dog, has the sweetest demeanor and does not have a care in the world. She enjoys a good head scratch and will nuzzle you to say, "More please!" She does great with other dogs and gets along with cats. She loves a good chew toy and almost always has a ball in her mouth. While she plays well with others, she can also be protective of her toys when other dogs are around. She is working on not guarding her toys and releasing a toy when asked. Martha is an older girl, but she does not let her age slow her down. She enjoys going on walks and chasing lizards in the backyard. She walks well on the leash, comes when called, and sits when asked. She is currently working on her stay command. Martha is a nap queen and is perfectly content sleeping the day away at your feet or in her own bed. She does have a bit of arthritis in her back that makes her a little bit stiff and unstable after being stationary for an extended amount of time. She does not show signs of being in pain and once she gets moving her stability improves. Martha is currently on a joint supplement which helps. Martha can get a little excited about food and is working on taking food gently from the hand. Because of this, she would do best in a home without small children. Martha is heartworm positive and is undergoing treatment. She is adoptable but will not be moved into her forever home until she has completed treatment. Martha 90 lbs of pure love and is looking for a forever home that will fully love her in return. She is house trained, crate trained, and up to date on vaccines. As a senior, Martha's standard adoption donation is $250, but $150 for a senior adopter 65+ through our Seniors for Seniors program.

animal.description:
Willie is a lanky pup with golden short, soft hair. He has splashes of white including on his face and toes, floppy ears, a long tail, and the kindest brown eyes.
 Willie has earned a nickname of Gentleman Willie! His calm demeanor is so comforting. He is very low key and mostly enjoys being around people, but doesn't like to be the center of attention. Willie is shy, but warms up when you sit beside him or crouch next to him and give him head pats. Chin scratches are his favorite! 
Willie gets along great with his foster dog brother, although isn't much interested in playing yet. He does well around other dogs and seems to be more comfortable around them than he is with people at first.
Willie's dog bed is his favorite part of the house. Most days you'll find him lounging in his dog bed, always with his paws crossed (see photos). 
He is mostly house-trained and crate-trained. He goes outside to take care of his business, sniffs around for a few minutes, then comes back inside to the warm house. His favorite place to sleep is his dog bed. We crate him when we're away from the house for a few hours. Otherwise, Willie does not need to be crated during the day, as he roams the house without any issues. 
Morning times are when he's most full of energy! He runs around in circles and wags his tail vivaciously (check him out in the video from Christmas morning!).
Willie is learning to walk on a leash and has made such big improvements as we've worked with him! He is scared of loud noises, like cars driving by. Following IARs shy dog protocol is key to his success: We recommend using a double-leash method when walking Willie: one leash on his collar and one leash on his harness or a slip lead. Having two leashes will ensure he remains in your care even if gets spooked during his walk. He gets more and more brave every day! 
Willie isn't a high energy dog, so he would be happy with an apartment or a house. Because of his fear of loud noises, Willie would love a quiet environment to call home so he is able to relax more easily and come out of his shell.
 If you're looking for low-key companion, Willie is your guy!
 Willie came into IAR from a rural shelter.
 Read more about Willie on the Independent Animal Rescue website at https://animalrescue.net/dogs/d-20-221/.

animal.description:
I'm a 2 year old, 14 pound, Chihuahua looking for my best forever friend. Here's what we know so far!

I'm still getting used to my surroundings at the moment with my new foster, and my personality hasn't felt safe to shine through yet. What I can tell you is that I'm timid around these new giants. I am sweet when I feel relaxed. I get along with the household cat. I'm still working on my bathroom manners, but have made lots of progress in the past few days. I do okay in a crate, but if you have to leave me, I prefer a more open space like a bathroom.

I've had a few hiccups in my past that has lead me to a mild case of heartworms, but don't worry, it's not as scary as it sounds. I'm on the mend and I have a dedicated team to get me all better again.

I'm quiet. I don't have a lot to say and I don't take up much room. I just want to snuggle up and get belly rubs. What can I say?? I'm the perfect companion!

Fill out an application http://rescuedogvillage.com/forms/RDV/frm_adopt-rdv-cp.html to be considered as a potential forever home through our rescue. PLEASE NOTE APPLICATION: you will need to type the address in the address bar because live DOG NAME : LUNA RDV 937 DOG GENDER: Female AGE: 2 Years Old WEIGHT: 70 Pounds BREED: German Shepherd LOCATION: Alabama Gulf Coast ADOPTION FEE: $550.00 (includes transport) EMAIL: For more information about this dog, contact email : ausman@gulftel.com EMAIL: For more information about this dog, contact: RescueDogVillage@yahoo.com APPLICATION: If this dog has stolen your heart, don't wait! Please apply online now to be considered as a potential adopter. PLEASE NOTE: All the information about this dog is in the bio. If you have not summited an application and are waiting for a response from us by email, please understand that applications are coming in every day and are being processed ahead of you. Therefore, the longer you wait for questions to be answered, the less your chances are. In addition, as home life and rescue put the needs of our rescue dogs first, we regret that we were not able to get back to you. LEASH, BASIC COMMAND AND HOUSE TRAINED SPAYED, FULLY VETTED AND CHIPPED LONG FLOWING COAT Her name is Luna, her breed is German shepherd, her appearance is breathtaking and she is available for adoption! This young lady (2 years) has had a tough start in life but she has managed to not only survive but excel. Luna is extremely bright, highly focused, very loving, loyal to a fault and totally committed to her person. Our girl is very well trained in behavioral commands, she great on the leash a superbly house trained. Luna performed very well in all aspects of our socialization and training programs. Her training has revealed a very high intelligence, an affinity for training, very good social skills with adults and well behaved dogs. Luna's training also revealed a less than infinite patience with highly active toddlers, also revealed is a solid resistance to being dominated by other large dogs. The things said, this great girl would thrive in a house of adults with well-behaved dogs. As a trainer and handler I have found Luna to be very affectionate, very easy to train and a pleasured to be around. About Our Rescue Whether you adopt through Rescue Dog Village Guardian, Inc A 5013c Non-Profit Organization or any other similar organization, the LEAST we can do is thank you from the bottom of our hearts for considering welcoming these deserving dogs into your hearts and home. One of our favorite sayings is "RESCUE IS THE BEST BREED," and we believe that wholeheartedly. Help us help these dogs and submit your application today! We appreciate that you want to help make a difference in the lives of dogs who need us most!!! RESCUE ROCKS! Disclaimer: Please note that the breeds posted on our dogs' biographies are our best guess based on years of working with rescue dogs. Adopters who need to know the exact breed or mix of breeds of a particular dog must have the dog's DNA tested at their own expense.
To see more photos of this dog and all our adoptable dogs,
please check out our website at Rescue Dog Village.
RESCUE DOG VILLAGE GUARDIAN, INC A 5013C NON-PROFIT ORGAINZATION WEBSITE: WWW.RESCUEDOGVILLAGE.COM OUR DOGS ARE MICRO-CHIPPED AND READY TO BE PART OF YOUR FAMILY TODAY! These dogs deserve all of our attention, and in Rescue Dog Village Guardian, Inc A 5013c Non-Profit Organization, we are committed to our adopters and our dogs equally. We offer full disclosure and hope to make the best matches possible. Please know our adoption fees never cover our expenses. We rely on the generosity of our adopters and supporters to help us help the dogs. Our rescue is only in the business of offering full disclosure to adopters, and expects and hopes to engage your questions and concerns fully. We owe it to the dogs we rescue and all the wonderful families/adopters who might consider welcoming our charges into their hearts and home. Our dogs are waiting for that ideal forever home where they will be cherished as deserving family members. It's sad these second chances are even necessary for these dogs, but we are committed to them and will devote the time and energy to their re-homing, and not just move them to save more dogs. We diligently and responsibly seek good matches, as we don't want to re-home the dog again. These animals have already endured more than they should have, and through no fault of their own. It behooves us to be honest and forthright, and we appreciate the same in return from applicants. It's that winning combination of reciprocal trust and respect that allows for successful placements to be made. Happy adopters translate to happy dogs, and that's our goal!

animal.description:
*Please read the full bio*
If you are interested in meeting me , we require an approved application. If you have questions regarding adoption, please visit our website --> www.adoptionfirstanimalrescueky.com Please do not email us asking if the dog is available, if they are on pet finder. We will not respond to emails that can be answered on our website.
Hi. My name is Luka. I came to the rescue when I was 5 weeks old. I am now approx 6 months old. I had to leave my mommy because a bigger dog got too rough with me and hurt my eye. The doctor says it's all better now and I can see just fine. I'm your typical bully pup. I act like a big tough guy but deep down I am a big softie. I love to snuggle and play all day. I would love a family that loves to be outdoors and does lots of active things. I have a lot of energy and I get bored when I'm stuck in the house. I don't always behave myself when I get too bored. Often times, I like to pester the cats. My foster mom isn't too happy when I do that. What can I say, it's fun and I don't hurt them. They like to run around just like me and I can't resist the urge to chase them. My momma says I'm real smart boy too. I already know how to sit and give her my paw when she tells me to. I am working on potty training. I get too distracted and just can't hold it. I'm getting better and I'm sure I will stop having accidents in the house soon. I'm a quick learner. Anyhow, I would love to find my forever family. If you have space in your home and heart for a cute guy like me, I'd love to join your family!!

Complete Application

You must complete the adoption application in full to be considered for adoption. 

Home Check

All adoptions do require a home check. If you are not comfortable with a home check please do not apply. We want to ensure the safety of our dogs and to make sure the adoptive family is comfortable. 

Meet and Greet

If your application has been approved we will schedule a meet and greet for the dog of your choice or for a few we think might be a good fit for your family. 

Sign Adoption Contract

This must be read and signed prior to adoption.

Adoption Fee 

Once everything has been reviewed the adoption fee will need to be paid. Puppies under 6 months is $300, over 6 months is $250, over 10 years is $150. Adoption fee includes: -Spay or Neuter -Microchip (additional registration fee required to transfer ownership to adopters) -Up to date on vaccinations -All animals have been examined by a veterinarian ** All adoption fees are non refundable.

animal.description:
12/30/20 Welcome to STAF, Sam Elliot! Sam was taken in as a stray by a kind heart, and then brought to STAF to find his forever home. A real lover of life, Sammy is an exuberant soul when it comes to play and affection. Our volunteers are working on his leash skills ... he will benefit from some basic obedience training. He is only around 1 1/2 years old (est. birthdate 6/19) and weighs in the mid-fifties. Please check back for updates as we get to know him better. Visit STAF.org for more information on our adoption process.

•  All of our animals are spayed/neutered and current on shots.
•  We do not do same-day adoptions. You will be asked to return for at least one follow-up visit, then take the dog home for a trial period before officially adopting. 
•  You must be 21 years or older to adopt from STAF.
•  We require a 4-foot-tall physical fence for homes with children under the age of 11. We also may require a physical fence for specific dogs on a case-by-case basis, depending on each dog’s behavior and exercise needs.
•  Due in part to increasing coyote activity/incidents in the area and the difficulty of predicting how a dog will respond to invisible fence training, we can not adopt to homes with invisible fences.
•  We do request vet and personal references.
•  We can facilitate adoptions within a 75-mile radius of our Cincinnati-based shelter.

animal.description:
If you see a dog listed on Petfinder, then that dog is currently available in our rescue. You don't need to email asking if they are available. 
The crucial first step is to fill out an application @www.camorescue.com

ALL adoptions require a completed application, vet check, home check and final contract.  The application to adopt can be found at www.camorescue.com.

Meet Lilly!  Lilly is a 2-3 year old silky yorkie weighing 15lbs.   She will work well with a family that will have  patience to earn her trust. She will gravitate quicker to kids and will be fine with or without other dogs.  She is crate and potty trained, she is a quiet dog and does not bark a lot.  She loves her daily walks and loves to sleep in her crate next to her person.

Adoption fees are variable. Up to date vaccines, microchip, spay/neuter are included in the fee.

Once your application has been approved, we will put you in touch with the foster to set up a  meet and greet. We are a foster based RESCUE, not a shelter. All of our dogs are in individual foster homes. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We select the best applicant for each dog, based on the dog's needs. 
For the safety of our small breed dogs and based on our past experiences, we will not place our dogs in homes with large breed dogs.    

CAMO rescue is a 501c3 whose primary focus is rescuing small dogs from the euthanasia list from high kill TX shelters.   
EIN # is 46-5486022
We rescue 800+ animals a year.

Follow us on Facebook at www.facebook.com/camorescue

Our donation link is http://www.paypalme/camorescue 

We are strictly volunteer based, no salaries are paid and 100% of donations go towards rescuing dogs.

animal.description:
Hi everybody, my name is Rory and I have a dog-gone UNBELIEVABLE story for you.

I am a sweet, loving girl who is looking for my forever home! But I have a secret, and a story that sets me apart from the other dogs here at Lost Our Home. You have to promise not to tell anyone. This is strictly CLASSIFIED stuff. Here's the deal... I am a real life time traveler. But I don't know HOW I got here to 2021, or why my time machine won't take me back to where I came from.

Once upon a paw, far away and long ago, I was just a sweet innocent young pup living my life, the world was my oyster! I was the most pup-ular girl in the neighborhood, shared dinners with the likes of Andy Warhowl, Bark Twain, and even the infamous Droolius Caesar. Ah, life was simpler back then. And then, out of NOWHERE, one day I woke up on the street, with these things called CARS whizzing by, and people wearing muzzles on their faces, and holding weird square boxes up to their ears instead of looking at each other! Ever since that day I've had a pretty ruff time. Thankfully, I know how to keep up a pawsitive attitude and make the most of things.

You will find me waiting pretty and proper with my favorite little teddy bear in my mouth. It's the only thing I have with me still from my old life and it brings me comfort. I love my toys and I sure love to show them off, I really don't think it's too much to ask for a family to spoil me with lots of toys (squeaky ones) and affection because I am a silly pup stuck in a big girl body!! 

I'd love to be your one and only pet, I'm not the best at sharing the spotlight. This new age world has some crazy things that really scare me, like TVs, vacuums, and dishwashers. But you can't blame me, I'm not even from this century! I'm a simple dog who needs a slow introduction to these fast-changing times! I love my kennel because it helps me feel safe at night, and I am very much potty trained in a home. I get anxious when left alone, but that's just because I have a love for people that LOVE ME.

If you are looking to open your heart to once in a LIFETIME pet who can share the secrets of the past with you, while we walk hand in paw into the future together, please take the time to apply to meet me! I can't wait for the op-paw-tunity to meet you!

All dog adoptions include the following:
--Spay/neuter surgery
--All current vaccinations
--Microchip with free chip registration
--Free wellness exam through VCA Animal Hospitals
--Access to our Behavior Helpline for the lifetime of the pet
 
For more information or to schedule an appointment to meet this pet, please complete a Dog Adoption Questionnaire online. You can also email us at adoptions@lostourhome.org.

animal.description:
Rocky is 3 years old and weighs 60lbs.
Rocky is a very smart boy, learns fast, and responds well to positive praise. He wants to please his people and will if you show him what you expect. He is good with other dogs and enjoys playing with them and going for walks with them. He knows his basic commands. He does pull on leash when he sees something he wants, usually another dog he wants to say hello to. 
Rocky can get excited when he sees you and jump up, but will immediately stop when reminded its not good manners. He needs an owner willing to exercise him and play fetch to drain some of his energy. Daily walks would be great. He loves to jog and is great at keeping the pace of the person he is running with. Once he has been exercised he is happy to just hang out with his people.
Rocky lives with two other dogs in his foster home and does well with them. He does however have a tendency to guard his food bowl from them if it is left out after eating. The remedy is to remove the bowl and he will forget about it. He needs structured feeding time where he eats, then the bowl is put away until it is time to eat again. He does take treats nicely with the other dogs when his foster has them all sit and take turns. He takes treats very gently from his human and doesn't show any aggression.
Rocky is vaccinated, microchipped, and neutered. He is house trained and will use a crate if needed. He would love an active home where he is included in the activities. He needs a fully fenced yard with a standard 6ft fence. We suggest middle aged children and older, no cats. 
If you think you can offer Rocky the stable home he deserves please submit an application to www.takemehomedogrescue.org

animal.description:
Sadie was left chained to her dog house with her puppies. She was starving, full of fleas and worms. After treatment she was spayed and put on heartworm treatment. She is now ready for adoption! She is very sweet and friendly, would love to live in someone's house and be a couch potato. She's overly attentive to our cats and small dogs but has not attempted to hurt them. It would be best if she was in a home as an only dog or with other dogs her size. She is eight years old and just wants to relax and enjoy her senior years in a home being loved the way she deserves to be. 

All adult dogs are spayed/neutered, have a rabies certificate, vaccinations, heartworm negative and are dewormed. Puppies are vaccinated and dewormed and will come with a voucher for spay/neuter and final shots. When you adopt you will make a donation to help defray the cost of that expense. You must fill out and application and become a member of True Blue Animal Rescue in order to adopt. Email help@t-bar.org for more information.

animal.description:
Kane is a super laid back guy who loves going on walks and playing with his toys.  He adores people, gets along great with other dogs, and is just a cool, gentle dude.  He is 2 years old and heartworm negative, and his adoption fee includes his neuter and microchip. If interested, please call the shelter at 281-403-8707 to schedule an appointment and/or request an application.  If you have specific questions, you can e-mail mc.rescueme@gmail.com, but we *cannot* schedule an appointment by e-mail or from a message on this page - you must call the shelter for a meet and greet.

We have transport options, but only to homes without other pets (because we have no way to make sure our dogs are compatible with your pets). We are in the Houston area but can transport to most of Texas, Washington State, Oregon, Maine, Alabama, Tennessee, Virginia, Maryland, Pennsylvania, Massachusetts, Rhode Island, Connecticut, New York, New Jersey, and Ohio. If you live somewhere else and are interested in adopting, just ask, and maybe we can work out alternative arrangements. Please don't hesitate to contact us with any questions.

Online Adoption Application 

Meet Xena!

Hi, I'm a beautiful, dainty young girl. I might be a shepherd mix. With all the changes that have went on in my life lately, I'm confused and scared of everything but I'm trying really hard and in a short amount of time I've opened up alot to my foster parents and foster fur-siblings.

I am looking for a calmer, quieter home with a loving, patient family that will give me the time and attention I need to adjust to my new family, routines, smells, sounds and environment. An active family will do after I have settled in and have gained your trust. I think I will do best in a home with other other dogs to teach me not to be so scared of everything and how to be a good doggy. Because I like to run away from things I'm scared of, I will need a physical fenced in yard to play in and burn off my puppy energy. I just want to be loved.
